# VRodos Plugin — AI Agent Rules (Cursor / Copilot)

> Full rules are in `CLAUDE.md` at the project root. Read it BEFORE writing code.

## Critical CSS Rule

DaisyUI component classes DO NOT WORK due to a double-prefix bug in tailwind.config.js.
Only Tailwind utilities (tw-* prefix), inline <style> blocks, and manual CSS work reliably.

Broken: d-tabs, d-skeleton, d-join, d-collapse, d-tooltip, d-badge, d-card, d-alert, d-menu, d-dropdown
Working (hand-styled only): d-btn, d-checkbox, d-radio, d-modal, d-input, d-select, d-range

## Quick Reference

- Tailwind prefix: tw-
- DaisyUI prefix: d- (only with manual CSS backing)
- Icons: Lucide (<i data-lucide="name">) — call lucide.createIcons() after dynamic DOM changes
- Category icons: single source of truth in js_libs/vrodos_icons.js
- Camera: envir.orbitControls.object (NOT envir.camera)
- Selection: mouseup with 5px drag threshold
- Always null-guard transform_controls.object
- CSS auto-builds via npm run watch:css — DO NOT manually rebuild
- Templates output full HTML pages (DOCTYPE), not WP shortcodes

See CLAUDE.md for complete rules.
